				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing the Neriad Shaw<a name="40173"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 16 04 5:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I was able to solo for the shawl recently, although it took me 22 sea princess kills to get it. From what I experienced...
<br />
A neriad sea princess is a rare spawn, and can spawn anywhere a neriad maiden does. A neriad weaver is a rare spawn anywhere a neriad mistress can spawn. Now...the sea princess is the one that dropped the shawl for me, and she isn't too terrible to fight (except that she summons). A neriad weaver, however...they HURT, lol. She hits lots harder and stuns aoe before she summons, and she seems to summon alot more than the princess (oh and she sees invis too, so fading doesn't work well, and she seems alot more magic resistant than the other neriads). Unfortunately camping the shawl you can run across a weaver...my only death down there was due to a weaver, in fact...<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />You can avoid possible weaver spawns by just camping the first two neriads in the big open like area underwater if you want to and save yourself the headache. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />
What I did was selo's myself outside (the long lasting selo's)...then zone in and da. Jump in the water and head right, till you see a big opening with 2 swordfish or seahorse mobs, one on either side of the walls. There, you'll want to hug left. Fade, and be on the lookout for neriads, because 2 will be in front of you. I used Snare, Wind of Marr, Fufil's Diminishing Dirge (to help lower MR on them, they can be very magic resistant)...I would lull when necessary and I had charm up too, in case things went bad. Also had Requiem of Time up as well, along with mezz in case I needed to mezz and twist regen. Technically, you could camp the first 2 neriads you come to and not mess with any other ones, but the tunnels past the area you land in with two neriads has lots of neriads in it, and they can be lulled and pulled if you feel up to it. I melee'd and twisted my songs, and left Fufil's out of the twist if I got a little low (weavers mainly). The main area is a big one, and you can probably kite those 2 in the area you first come to if you wanted (charm kiting there is a pain becuase neriads like to break charm early alot, but it can be done as well). Oh, pulling with dispell also seemed to help me land slow and snare easier as well. Snare them though, they do run at low health, and like to swim to the top of the water there, luring you to follow them and to aggro three sirens up there (/whistle, I didn't do that, nooo, hehe...they won't go on land, thankfully, so you can stay back to avoid doing that to yourself. The sea princess is the only one I've heard of that will go on land, and none of the 22 I fought ever ran at low health).
<br />
Hope all that mishmash helps some...it's great fun now annoying my guildies being in water elemental form all the time. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
