				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing the Neriad Shaw<a name="40392"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 8:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Any neriad WILL go on land if it is fleeing... and they are social with all other creatures, in my experience. Neriad fleeing - snare = death.. FM will not help you in this situation :(
<br />

<br />
There's an easy place to single pull these, but its only a 4-spawn camp.
<br />
Zone in from CS.
<br />
DA, invis, run and jump into the water and swim right.
<br />
Straight ahead through tunnel, there's a wall in front of you with a hole in it slightly to the right. swim into that hole and hop out of the water and FM.
<br />
Invis again (look out for a siren in very close proximity) and move carefully through the siren room to the rope bridge (siren princess will see invis)
<br />
cross bridge, move down ramp tunnels till you reach the pool.
<br />
There are 2 neriads in this pool.
<br />
Remain invis, jump in water and swim through the tunnel connected to the pool. you will pass 1... then another neriad on the way until you reach an empty underwater room. 
<br />
You can easily pull to, and engage in this area. Its where I did mine - but I didn't solo it, I duo'd with another bard.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
