				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing the Neriad Shaw<a name="41360"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 22 04 4:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can easily kite most of these mobs. From others advice I've avoided the weavers.
<br />

<br />
To get there, jump in water, and hug the wall to your right when facing away from zone in.  Stick to it, screw suicide DA, don't forget we can lull. Pretty much everything between u and neriads see's invis. Keep following wall till your at an opening guarded by 2 horses (watch out there is a roamer around here). Lull your way past the horses, This area is roamer free. Go either way to duel 2 neriad spawns. I used charm to kill off the first 2. Then pull 1 at a time and kite the rest. It is possible to do this without snare (200 swim put me far ahead of them) but the pathing sucks, so snare is advised, especially at around 30%.
<br />

<br />
The princess is around lvl 55, and a warrior. She was a h*ll fight for me. Both times I soloed her the following happened: During a mez/regen break, she would instantly regen about 40% of her life. On the frist kill she did it 3 times all when between 10-15% life. The second kill she regened at 40% life up to 80%, and then full hp about 20 sec later. I saw NO cast messages of any kind, she was not a caster herself. There were also no mobs around, each time she was in a different area.
<br />

<br />
Anyways this camp sucks, I called in a cleric for the 3rd fight and still haven't gotten drop yet *shakes fist*
<br />

<br />
Don't forget your EB item!</span></td>
