				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing the Neriad Shaw<a name="52750"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 2:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just got mine today easiest way I have found so far is the normal method for getting down to the camp. ie turn right at zone and head to neriad spawn and fade.  When I got there set up snare/full set of chants/Requim/mez and regen clear the first one by pulling with slow then chant it while tanking.  Leave yourself a little more life than usual to do mez/heal break for the DoTs to wear off.  After first one in room is dead pull the 2nd with snare then use 2 chants followed by snare then next 2 chants then snare while swimming the outside edge of the room.  I avoided most melee damage that way and was able to clear more spawns.  Same strat with the princess even though she summons just helps to not be in range all the time you still avoid some damage and was able to kite her down with no mez/mana break several times.  With this method I was able to clear 6 to 8 spawns depending on the pop and I even took down a dreaded weaver.  Took 26 princesses to get my shawl and had a crazy 15ac 10wis 45hp 45mana cloak drop 2 times before I ever saw the shawl.  Hope this helps someone and good luck this camp sucked.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
